<br>
It's quite a leap to say that names are petitioned because of roleplayers.  People can petition names for all sorts of reasons ranging from offensiveness to stupdity of the name to pet peeves, to whatever.  The one question I have, is how is it that someone's fun in EQ can be entirely ruined by having their name changed?  I have a hard time visualizing  someone's entire world revolving around the fact that their character is named &quot;Slapmywilly&quot; in game...<br>
<br>
No, I did not petition the turtles, no I am not saying that they should have been petitioned - we considered naming my Vah Shir Cheetara, and my husband's Iksar Koopa Kabana for laughs, so we aren't entirely innocent on this front -  but I am saying that I think coming here and proclaiming RPers at fault, and deeming them fun smashing &quot;fucktards&quot; might be taking it a bit over the edge.  For all we know, the creator of the Ninja Turtles plays on FV and didn't want to see their creations in game.<br>
<br>
